purposes**, including SaaS offerings, internal enterprise operations, and resale
of Licensee’s own products incorporating the Work.

2.2 **License Models**  
The Agreement may be executed under one or more models:

(a) **Per-Organization License**  
   Licensee may deploy unlimited instances of the Work within a single legal
   entity, including subsidiaries expressly listed in the Purchase Order.

(b) **Per-Deployment License**  
   Licensee must obtain a license for each production Deployment.

(c) **Subscription License**  
   Time-limited commercial license including updates, support, and (optionally)
   Premium Modules.

2.3 **License Restrictions**  
Licensee may not:

- sublicense or redistribute the Work except as permitted in Section 2.1;  
- remove or tamper with copyright or attribution notices;  
- use the Work to create a competing AI automation platform;  
- use the Work, directly or indirectly, to build, operate, or
offer a competing agent marketplace, agent orchestration platform, or any
substantially similar service that competes with the HyperAgency Marketplace.
- offer the Work as a hosted service, unless expressly permitted
in writing by Vuics LLC.
- engage in any use prohibited by export or sanctions laws.

