6.5 Derivative Contributions

(a) Modifications to the Work (Mandatory Contribution)

Any extensions, enhancements, integrations, or plugins developed by Licensee that
modify, extend, or directly interact with the **HyperAgency source code or core OS**
must be offered to Vuics LLC for consideration for upstream inclusion.  
Vuics LLC may accept, reject, or modify such contributions at its discretion.  

Licensee grants Vuics LLC a perpetual, irrevocable, worldwide, non-exclusive
license to use, modify, and incorporate any such contributions into the Work.
Nothing in this clause obligates Licensee to assign ownership; Licensee retains
ownership of the submitted code.

Examples include, but are not limited to:

- New Bridges or Connectors (messaging, telephony, webhooks, cloud APIs)  
- OS Core Extensions (agent orchestration modules, deployment configuration, microservices code)  
- System-level Improvements (performance optimization, security hardening, scaling tools)  
- API/SDK Extensions that enhance or extend the Work’s core functionality  
- New agent archetypes or templates that modify the microservices framework of the Work

(b) Content Created on the Platform (Voluntary Contribution)

Licensee retains full ownership of any agents, HyperAgent Apps, workflows, or
other applications created using the Work that **do not modify the core source code**.  
Offering these creations to Vuics LLC for consideration for upstream inclusion is
**encouraged, but not required**.

For clarity:

- Contributions used solely for internal purposes, or not deployed/distributed,
  are exempt from the mandatory submission requirements.  
- Vuics LLC may accept, reject, or modify any submitted contributions at its discretion.

